equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object s)
Check if an Object s is equal to the actual Symbol. Equality is implemented as equality of the names of two Symbols.

Returns:
True, if s and the actual Symbol are equal, False otherwise or if s is not an instance of Symbol
See Also:
Object.equals(java.lang.Object)

clone

public java.lang.Object clone()
Return a clone of the actual Symbol. The cloning is restricted on the actual Symbol, what means that the pointers of the new Symbol have the same targets as the pointers of the actual Symbol (a shallow-clone is implemented).

Returns:
An Object equal to the actual Symbol
See Also:
Object.clone()
